text: Auburn is a city in Cayuga County, New York, United States. It is located at the north end of Owasco Lake, one of the Finger Lakes, in Central New York. As of the 2020 census, the city had a population of 26,866. It is the county seat of Cayuga County. ==References== Category:Cities in New York (state) Category:County seats in New York (state)
title: Auburn, New York
